# 3d-shaders / OpenUSD (usdrecord)

Author a deterministic OpenUSD stage as human-readable ASCII (`.usda`) and render it
headlessly to a PNG via `usdrecord` and Hydra's Storm delegate (Metal on macOS). The
`.usda` text is the version-controllable source; the PNG is the pixel deliverable.
Note: `pip install usd-core` provides Python authoring only — it does NOT ship the
`usdrecord` binary. A full OpenUSD build (`build_usd.py` with imaging+Hydra) or a
vendored prebuilt is required to render.

controls do
  openusd.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  openusd.scene: { label: "Scene (.usda)", type: "textarea", file: "src/scene.usda" }
  openusd.imageWidth: { label: "Image width (px)", type: "range" }
  openusd.renderer: { label: "Render delegate", type: "select", options: ["Storm", "Embree"] }
  openusd.complexity: { label: "Complexity", type: "select", options: ["low", "medium", "high", "veryhigh"] }
  openusd.camera: { label: "Camera prim path", type: "text" }
end

## Required reading
- OpenUSD official toolset docs (usdrecord) — Pixar / AOUSD, Apache-2.0 (mod, TOST):
  https://openusd.org/release/toolset.html
- NVIDIA Learn OpenUSD (install + Python authoring) — NVIDIA, vendor docs:
  https://docs.nvidia.com/learn-openusd/latest/usdview-install-instructions.html
- No OpenUSD-specific Anthropic skill exists: https://github.com/anthropics/skills

## Render
```bash
# Full OpenUSD build with imaging (one-time, ~30-60min; needs Xcode CLT + cmake):
git clone https://github.com/PixarAnimationStudios/OpenUSD
python OpenUSD/build_scripts/build_usd.py --no-tests /opt/openusd
export PATH=/opt/openusd/bin:$PATH
export PYTHONPATH=/opt/openusd/lib/python:$PYTHONPATH

# Verify the render binary exists BEFORE claiming render capability:
which usdrecord

# Render the stage to a PNG (Storm/Metal on macOS — no X server needed):
usdrecord --imageWidth 512 --renderer Storm src/scene.usda out/scene.png
file out/scene.png   # => PNG image data
```

## Failure modes
- `usdrecord: command not found` after `pip install usd-core` — expected; usd-core is
  authoring-only. Do a full `build_usd.py` (imaging enabled) or use a prebuilt.
- Blank / black PNG — no light or camera in the stage; add a `DistantLight` and ensure
  a default camera or pass `--camera`.
- Linux headless errors (Qt/GLFW/EGL) — set offscreen GL (EGL) or use `--disableGpu`
  with a CPU delegate; macOS Storm avoids this via Metal.
- Embree/RenderMan output is non-byte-deterministic (sampling noise) — prefer Storm
  raster for visual-regression stability.
- Prefer `.usda` (diffable ASCII) over `.usdc` (binary) in version control.
